Dr. Lakshmi Menon is very friendly and takes time to listen to your problems. The waiting time was reasonable, even when we were late for the appointment due to unforeseen traffic. And she was patient enough to listen to all our queries and provided all answers in a calm and constructive manner. It was a huge improvement from some of our previous doctors, who would give very blunt and careless remarks about our baby, which no parent would like to listen.

All in all, a great doctor who takes care of your little one with a smile always.

She tries to understand the complete child health history in her first few questions and later listens to the health issue.  She doesn't suggest antibiotics in the first go,  which is good for children.  Second thoughts not required in consulting her*  *** ** *** ****** *************

We simply adore n love the doctor. She is my daughters doctor since birth.  It's been 4 years. She is very courteous, sweet n to the point.  My daughter loves her too.  Anyone looking for pedeatrician can go to her without any hesitation.  Your bundle of joy will b in safe hands.

She first understood the whole history of my child.
She probed a lot about my child like where she was born was all her vacation done etc and then asked about the current problem and suggested relevant treatment and also explained why these medicine are give and told about the plan of action. These little things gave a lot of confidence.

Dr. Lakshmi Menon is quite friendly and easy to talk with. She takes time to understand the kid's history and patiently listens to parents before getting into a conclusion. We consulted her first for our daughter's eczema and thereafter she has been our kid's regular pediatrician. The support and care she gives is exemplary and doesn't give medicines or antibiotics if not required. Everytime we meet her she has the same positive energy which gives great peace of mind to us.
